{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The action of the idempotent 𝑒 𝑑 on 𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S is given by the image of 𝑒 𝑑 under the map𝑃 𝑑-1: Hom Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔,Sp) (𝑃 𝑑 ℎ S, 𝑃 𝑑 ℎ S) -→ Hom Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔,Sp) (𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S, 𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S).",
    "By adjunction there is an equivalence Hom Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔,Sp) (𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S, 𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S) ≃ Hom Exc 𝑑 -1 * (Sp 𝜔,Sp) (𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S, 𝑃 𝑑-1 ℎ S), and applying 𝜋 0 to the composite gives the map𝑅 Q (𝑑) 𝜋 0 (𝑃 𝑑 -1)⊗Q ----------→ 𝑅 Q (𝑑 -1).",
    "By Theorem 5.2 this is isomorphic to 𝐴 Q (𝑑) (𝑖 𝑑 -1) * ------→ 𝐴 Q (𝑑 -1),which sends 𝑒 𝑑 to zero.",
    "The result follows from the observation that the action of an idempotent is determined by its action on the homotopy category, [Lur17, Lemma 1.2.4.6, Warning 1.2.4.8].",
    "□ Lemma 6.2."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}